Ranch in Hollywood, Jack Pitts hammers and shapes the horseshoe, files a 
horse's hoof, and nails the shoe into place. The back of Pitts' truck carries 
all the equipment he needs to operate his free-lance farrier business, 
including a small forge and a portable anvil. THEODORA LITSIOS / For The Times 
</P>
