<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
</P>
<P>
FIRM TO DESIGN FIRE STATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Culver City Redevelopment Agency on Monday unanimously selected 
Wolff/Lang/Christopher Architects Inc. to design the replacement for downtown 
Fire Station No. 1. 
</P>
<P>
Agency staff cited the firm's experience, cost estimate and willingness to 
complete its drawings within nine months in supporting its selection, according 
to a staff report. The firm will be paid $252,000 for its design. 
</P>
<P>
The old station, at 9760 Culver Blvd. next to City Hall, is considered 
seismically unsafe, and its lot will become part of the new City Hall. The new 
station will be built about a block away, at the corner of Culver Boulevard and 
Irving Place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
