<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: RACEWAY BEGINS REGISTRATION FOR COORS STOCK CAR SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ventura Raceway will begin its open registration period for cars and 
drivers who wish to compete in the 1990 Coors Silver Bullet Stock Car Racing 
Series beginning Saturday at the Ventura Raceway offices at 2810 West Wooley 
Road in Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
All drivers and car owners must register early to reserve their car numbers, 
which will be assigned on a first-come, first-served basis for the racing 
season. 
</P>
<P>
The season opens Friday, March 30 at the Ventura Fairgrounds track. 
</P>
<P>
The raceway will hold a second registration day Saturday, March 24 at the 
raceway, with that day also being an open practice session for all classes of 
cars. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura Raceway track director Cliff Morgan said that over $60,000 of 
improvements have been made to the quarter-mile dirt oval for the upcoming 
season, which runs through Nov. 17. 
</P>
<P>
The racing season will consist of the Street Stock and Mini Stocks running 
Friday nights and the return of the United States Auto Club Western States 
Midget Series, the Winged Outlaw Mini Sprints, three-quarter Midgets, and the 
Ventura Motocross Series running on selected Saturday nights. 
</P>
<P>
Street Stock Oval Champ, Charles Utts of Camarillo and Mini Stock Oval Track 
and Figure-8 Champ, Rock Ake, Jr. of Moorpark are expected to defend their 1989 
titles. 
</P>
<P>
Camarillo's Jeff Bosley, the 1989 Street Stock Figure-8 champion will not 
defend his title because he is on active duty with the Navy and has been 
transfered out of the area for one year. 
</P>
<P>
Information: 656-1122. 
</P>
<P>
Tryouts for the Foothill Little League Senior Division (13-15 year-olds) will 
be held Saturday at 1 p.m. at Balboa Middle School in Ventura. Coaches are also 
being recruited. 
</P>
<P>
Information: 805-642-4111. 
</P>
