<HEADLINE>
<P>
CIF GIRLS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MONTGOMERY SCORES UPSET OVER LA HABRA, 51-44 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS KAISER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The knights upset the Highlanders, the division's top-seeded team, in a girls 
4-A CIF quarterfinal game at La Habra on Wednesday night, 51-44. 
</P>
<P>
Bishop Montgomery will face the winner of the Los Altos-West Torrance game in 
the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
The Knights (17-9) first scented victory after a 15-2 spurt that gave them a 
17-10 lead with 4:59 remaining in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Bishop Montgomery shot just 22% (seven for 31) from the field in the first half 
but still led at intermission, 21-20, taking advantage of 13 Highlander 
turnovers. 
</P>
<P>
La Habra (21-4) held a decided height advantage over Bishop Montgomery but 
couldn't get the ball inside to its 6-5 center, Zrinka Kristic, and two 6-1 
forwards, Ana Kristic and Leslie Ferguson. The Knights' tallest player was 6-0 
Keisa Smith. 
</P>
<P>
In the second half La Habra started well but still had trouble going inside 
against the Knights' defense. Bishop Montgomery held off a fourth-quarter 
Highlander run that effectively ended when Ferguson, who had averaged 16.1 
points a game, fouled out with 6:39 left. 
</P>
<P>
The Knights clinched the victory with a 10-2 run in a 3 1/2-minute stretch 
midway through the fourth quarter. That gave them a 48-38 lead with 1:35 
remaining. 
</P>
<P>
Junior point guard Lily Cabaleiro led Bishop Montgomery with 25 points, 
including eight in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 -- DENNIS KAISER 
</P>
</TEXT>
