HIGH SCHOOL BOYS' BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DIVISION I 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 78, San Dieguito 61 -- Clark James led the fourth-seeded Cavers with 
32 points and 20 rebounds at San Diego. Also for San Diego, Jerome Allen scored 
12 points and pulled down seven rebounds. Matt De la Pena (25) and Brian 
Malewicz (16) combined to lead San Dieguito. 
</P>
<P>
Patrick Henry 65, Castle Park 57 -- Castle Park had four players score in 
doubles figures. Unfortunately for Castle Park it had only five players score 
in the game. Butch Reese scored 14 points and grabbed 12 rebounds for Patrick 
Henry (22-4). Danny Kotnik added 13 points for the Patriots. 
</P>
<P>
DIVISION II 
</P>
<P>
San Pasqual 69, Mission Bay 45 -- San Pasqual won despite playing without Erik 
Meek, the second-leading scorer in the county, and having its No. 2 scorer play 
just 14 minutes because of foul trouble. 
</P>
<P>
Meek sprained his ankle Friday against Ramona and won't know until today if he 
will be able to play Friday against Crawford in the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
"Obviously, with an injury like that it's going to take a couple of weeks to 
heal," San Pasqual Coach Tom Buck said. 
</P>
<P>
Bryan Banner, the team's No. 2 scorer, got into foul trouble early and spent 
most of the game on the bench. Richard Stark (15 points) and John Koser (14) 
picked up the slack for San Pasqual (19-5). 
</P>
<P>
Gebel Anderson and Chris Smith had 12 points apiece for Mission Bay (4-17). 
</P>
<P>
Crawford 74, Grossmont 71 (OT) -- Crawford senior Tracy Halton, playing in a 
knee brace, celebrated his first game since Christmas-time by scoring 14 
points, three in overtime, to help lead the Colts at home. 
</P>
<P>
Halton was averaging 26.5 points a game before he suffered a knee injury and 
has been watching from the bench since December. One of his field goals 
traveled three-quarters of the length of the court, giving Crawford a five 
point halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
Grossmont missed the second end of a one-and-one to send the game into 
overtime. 
</P>
<P>
Marc Carter led the Colts (18-8) with 34 points and 23 rebounds. Grossmont was 
led by Kevin Simon's 34 points. Grossmont ended the season with a 13-10 mark. 
</P>
<P>
Helix 49, Serra 47 -- With the game tied at 47 and 10 seconds left in the game, 
Henry Lundy grabbed an offensive rebound and scored to give Helix the victory 
at home. Lundy led Helix with 17 points. Teammate Lloyd Lake added 16. For 
Serra, who was outscored, 12-6, in the second quarter, Desi Dixon had 19 
points. 
</P>
<P>
Torrey Pines 89, Hoover 53 -- Torrey Pines' press helped force 30 turnovers and 
the top-seeded Falcons routed visiting Hoover (5-20). Bill Schiebe scored 14 
points and Bart Brandenburg added 13 for Torrey Pines (25-3), which led, 45-23, 
at halftime. 
</P>
