<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: LAKEWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
EXPANSION AT RIVER PARK TO BE DEDICATED SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A free pancake breakfast will highlight the dedication Saturday morning of the 
newly expanded River Park in Lakewood. There also will be free pony and hay 
rides, children's games and live entertainment at the event, which begins at 9 
a.m. 
</P>
<P>
River Park sits beside the San Gabriel River north of the Lakewood Equestrian 
Center at Carson Street and stretches to Del Amo Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
It is connected by bicycle and hiking paths along the river to Liberty Park in 
Cerritos and El Dorado Park in Long Beach. In all, the three parks have 700 
acres of open and recreational space. 
</P>
<P>
The 24-acre expansion at River Park was paid for with $1.4 million in state and 
federal recreation grants. The expansion includes the addition of an outdoor 
amphitheater, three picnic pavilions, three children's play areas, a wildflower 
meadow, 400 new trees and expanded parking for 200 cars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
