</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Redoubt Volcano erupted without warning, sending gritty ash raining down south 
of Anchorage, and the Coast Guard demanded stepped-up precautions at an oil 
depot on Cook Inlet. The Drift River terminal had been ordered closed to guard 
against an oil spill being caused by a future eruption, but the Coast Guard 
relented and said the terminal must empty six of its seven storage tanks and 
have cleanup equipment ready. 
