ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; 
</P>
<P>
UCI RACES TO BENEFIT CHILDRENS' GROUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A morning of racing events at UC Irvine on Sunday will raise money for the 
Make-A-Wish Foundation of Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
The first annual UCI Anteaters Make-A-Wish Race Day Event will include a 5-K 
run, a 10-K wheelchair race, a 3-K walk and two cycling races that will feature 
professional and collegiate cyclists. 
</P>
<P>
The day will also include a local business product fair and a cycling safety 
program. Proceeds from the day will go to the local Make-A-Wish organization, a 
Newport Beach-based nonprofit group that works toward granting the wishes of 
children who have terminal or life-threatening illnesses. 
</P>
<P>
The day begins with registration for the 5-K run at 6:30 a.m. Participants must 
have collected at least $50 in pledges to participate. The 10-K wheelchair race 
will begin at 8:30 a.m. with the 3-K walk following at 9:15. Participants in 
the 3-K walk must have collected $25 worth of pledges to take part. 
</P>
<P>
The Celebrity Cycling Race will begin at 10 a.m. and the Collegiate Cycling 
Races will follow at 11. 
</P>
<P>
All races will begin at the university's physical science parking lot. 
</P>
<P>
The UCI cycling team and radio station KUCI will also benefit from money raised 
during the day. 
</P>
<P>
For information, call (714) 642-6782. GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
