<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGELS' MINTON ACCEPTS $850,000 DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Greg Minton, who had filed for free agency after the Angels declined to go to 
arbitration with him, agreed to a one-year contract with the club Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Minton's contract includes a base salary of $850,000, with incentive clauses 
worth as much as $100,000. 
</P>
<P>
Minton, 38, was 4-3 with eight saves and a 2.20 earned-run average in 62 relief 
appearances last season. He had filed for arbitration at $1,150,000 and the 
Angels had offered $780,000. He earned $630,000 in salary last season and 
$100,000 in bonuses. 
</P>
<P>
The right-handed pitcher joined the Angels as a free agent in June, 1987. He 
set a club record last season by pitching 105 2/3 innings without allowing a 
home run, a streak he started in 1988. HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
