<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
MATER DEI, CORONA DEL MAR BOYS TO PLAY SEMIFINAL GAMES IN O.C. FRIDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mater Dei and Corona del Mar high schools are the only county teams that will 
play home games in the semifinals of the Southern Section boys' basketball 
playoffs Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei, the top-seeded team in the 5-A division, will be the home team when 
the Monarchs play El Toro at Ocean View High School. Mater Dei played six games 
in Ocean View's gym this year, and won all six. 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar won a coin flip and will play host to Sherman Oaks Notre Dame at 
Estancia High School in the 3-A division. 
</P>
<P>
Five teams were sent out of the county for their semifinal games, including 
Laguna Beach, the top-seeded team in 2-A, which will travel to Rolling Hills 
High School to meet El Segundo. 
</P>
<P>
In 3-A, Estancia will play Lompoc at Cabrillo High School and Servite will 
travel to St. Bernard High School to take on Culver City. Edison will play 
Compton at Dominguez High School in 4-AA, and St. Margaret's will take on 
Bethel Christian at Quartz Hills High School in the Small Schools division. 
</P>
<P>
All games will start at 7:30. The semifinal pairings: 
</P>
<P>
5-AA Division 
</P>
<P>
St. Monica (23-5) vs. Lynwood (29-1) at Gahr High School 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach Poly (24-2) vs. Lakewood (18-10) at Long Beach City College 
</P>
<P>
5-A Division 
</P>
<P>
El Toro (22-5) vs. Mater Dei (28-1) at Ocean View High School 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena (23-5) vs. Loyola (21-3) at Redondo Union High School 
</P>
<P>
4-AA Division 
</P>
<P>
Dominguez (23-5) vs. Glendora (24-5) at Chino High School 
</P>
<P>
Edison (20-8) vs. Compton (21-6) at Dominguez High School 
</P>
<P>
4-A Division 
</P>
<P>
Burbank Burroughs (18-6) vs. Artesia (23-2) at Cerritos College 
</P>
<P>
San Marcos (23-6) vs. La Mirada (19-8) at Biola College 
</P>
<P>
3-AA Division 
</P>
<P>
Estancia (18-9) vs. Lompoc (21-5) at Cabrillo High School in Lompoc 
</P>
<P>
Servite (16-10) vs. Culver City (17-9) at St. Bernard High School 
</P>
