<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ESTANCIA'S EARLE SCORES 42 IN VICTORY AT LOMPOC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Guard Melody Earle scored 42 points to lead Estancia to a 71-60 victory 
Wednesday over Lompoc in a 3-AA playoff game at Lompoc. 
</P>
<P>
The victory over the division's third-seeded team gave Estancia a 14-12 mark 
for the season. Lompoc finished at 21-4. 
</P>
<P>
Earle had 27 of her points in the first half, including a twisting 3-point 
basket at the buzzer to give Estancia a 34-31 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
The teams were tied at 48 after three periods, but the Eagles outscored Lompoc 
23-12 in the final period. 
</P>
<P>
Center Nicki Manzo scored 30 points for Lompoc, but Lompoc had trouble getting 
the ball to its inside players in the final period, according to Lompoc Coach 
Sherman Hanson. 
</P>
<P>
"We just didn't get the ball to our big people. That was our plan, to get our 
big people involved in the fourth period," Hanson said. 
</P>
<P>
In the 2-AA: 
</P>
<P>
Santa Margarita 63, Beaumont 48 -- Guard Kristen Mulligan scored 32 points, 19 
of them in the second half, to lead visiting Santa Margarita. Forward Sarah 
Witte had 22 for Santa Margarita (20-6), which will face Santa Ynez, a 64-33 
winner over St. Anthony's. Beaumont finished at 17-7. Santa Margarita led just 
27-24 at halftime, but used a tenacious defense to pull away in the final two 
periods. The Eagles outscored Beaumont 17-12 in the third period and 19-10 in 
fourth. Diane Terrill had 12 points for Beaumont. 
</P>
<P>
In the Small Schools: 
</P>
<P>
Ribet Academy 74, Cal Lutheran 58 -- Kate Stoll scored 29 points to lead the 
Fighting Frogs. Cal Lutheran finished 14-1. Becky Clark scored 14 points and 
Kim Floyd scored 13 for Ribet Academy (16-5). Cal Lutheran had an 18-10 
advantage after the first quarter, but Ribet Academy outscored Cal Lutheran 
25-12 in the second quarter and 24-18 in the third quarter to take control of 
the game. 
</P>
