<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION GIRLS' SOCCER PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
CANYON FENDS OFF WOODBRIDGE IN OVERTIME, 1-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HEATHER SMALLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kim Campbell scored the only goal in Canyon High School's 1-0 overtime victory 
overWoodbridge in the second round of the Southern Section 3-A girls' soccer 
playoffs Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
By the time the second 10-minute overtime period began, Canyon had taken 15 
shots on goal, and Woodbridge three. 
</P>
<P>
Then, with only a few minutes left, Warrior goalie Michelle Helring slid out in 
front of the ball, which bounced off of her and away. Fullback Deanna Doolittle 
ran in to cover and struck the ball with an arm. 
</P>
<P>
The sideline referee called a hand ball, and Campbell was awarded a penalty 
kick. The freshman forward shot a perfect arc over Helring for the game's only 
goal, and her 34th of the season. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon (15-0-4) almost scored again a minute later, but forward Mary Wilson's 
shot hit the top of the goal, and Kim Studley's shot off the rebound went way 
over. 
</P>
<P>
After the match, Woodbridge Coach William Bell was distraught about the call 
that led to the winning goal, saying the call was too close to allow it to 
decide a playoff game. 
</P>
<P>
Asked if he had seen the touch, Bell said, "I saw touches and pushes the whole 
game. Look, that's my opinion, and you know what everyone says about opinions. 
They're an outstanding team. Our job was to shut them out until overtime, and 
take it to a shoot out." 
</P>
<P>
In other 3-A matches: 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei 4, Long Beach Poly 0 -- Mater Dei (22-2) held Long Beach Poly to five 
shots and goalie Julie Tarney got her 19th shutout of the season. Katie Ward, 
Robyn Camarillo, Kim Conter and Amber Escobedo scored for Mater Dei, which led, 
2-0, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Troy 3, Buena 1 -- Jenny Scanlon scored all three goals to lead visiting Troy 
(15-3-3). It was the seventh time this season that Scanlon has scored three or 
more goals in a game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
