<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIZON VOTED ORANGE EMPIRE MVP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vince Hizon, who helped lead Cypress College to the Orange Empire Conference 
men's basketball title, was named the conference's most valuable player in a 
vote by the coaches. 
</P>
<P>
Hizon, a 6-foot-2 sophomore swingman from Mater Dei High School, averaged a 
team-high 15.2 points a game for Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
He also had 3.7 rebounds, 2.3 assists a game as well as shooting 56% from the 
field and 86% from the free-throw line. 
</P>
<P>
Hizon was joined on the 11-man team by teammates Grayle Humphrey and Eric 
Pauley. Don Johnson of Cypress was named the coach of the year. 
</P>
<P>
Also named to the team were Gene Altamirano, Matt Lien and Corie Blount of 
Rancho Santiago; Ric Van Scoyce and Alex Kreps of Golden West, Alan Schlines of 
Orange Coast, Rashone Lewis of Fullerton, and Dave Stienstra of Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
Donna Gondringer of Golden West College was named the most valuable women's 
player of the Orange Empire Conference in a vote of the coaches. 
</P>
<P>
Gondringer, a 6-foot-1 sophomore forward, averaged 15.6 points and 7.7 rebounds 
a game in leading the Rustlers to the conference title. 
</P>
<P>
Claudette Jackson and Bits Sirchia of Golden West also made the team. Golden 
West's Dick Stricklin was the coach of the year. 
</P>
<P>
Others named to the team were Michelle Hennessey, Erika Manning and Cindy 
Kollar of Orange Coast; Angie Nelsen, Candi Burnett of Fullerton, Shannon 
Garnos of Saddleback, Carolyn Burns of Rancho Santiago and Wendy Luebbers of 
Riverside. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
