<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA WEDNESDAY'S TRADES; 
</P>
<P>
CHEEKS DEALT FOR STRICKLAND; CARROLL TO NUGGETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The New York Knicks traded backup point guard Rod Strickland to the San Antonio 
Spurs on Wednesday for veteran guard Maurice Cheeks. 
</P>
<P>
Strickland, 23, a second-year pro, had expressed unhappiness with his role as a 
backup to Mark Jackson earlier this season and asked to be traded. He averaged 
8.2 points and 4.3 assists while playing 20 minutes per game. 
</P>
<P>
Cheeks, 33, was traded from Philadelphia to San Antonio last summer after 
spending his 11-year NBA career with the 76ers. He averaged 10.9 points and six 
assists in 35 minutes per game with the Spurs. In his 11 seasons with the 
76ers, Cheeks averaged 12.2 points and 7.3 assists in 853 games and leads 
active players in steals. 
</P>
<P>
Cheeks is expected to back up Jackson. Strickland likely will assume the 
starting point guard role with the second-place Spurs. 
</P>
<P>
The New Jersey Nets traded center Joe Barry Carroll to the Denver Nuggets for 
rookie guard Michael Cutright and acquired center Chris Dudley from the 
Cleveland Cavaliers in exchange for two second-round draft picks. 
</P>
<P>
Cleveland then packaged the draft choices from the Nets to acquire Derrick 
Chievous from the Houston Rockets. 
</P>
<P>
Dudley, a fourth-round selection from Yale in the 1987 draft, averaged five 
points and 5.5 rebounds in 37 games with Cleveland this season. The 6-foot-11 
Dudley started the season on the injured list with a broken bone in his left 
wrist and was activated Nov. 15. 
</P>
<P>
Carroll entered the NBA after being drafted by Golden State with the first pick 
in the first round of the 1980 NBA draft. After playing six seasons with the 
Warriors, he was traded to Houston in December of 1987, then went to New Jersey 
in November of 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Carroll has played in 45 games for the Nets this season, starting 20, and has 
averaged 8.8 points, 5.4 rebounds and 21.8 minutes per game. In his nine-year 
career he has averaged 18.2 points and 7.8 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
The Rockets received three second-round draft picks and an undisclosed amount 
of cash from the Cavaliers for forward-guard Chievous. 
</P>
<P>
Also, the Rockets acquired guard Vernon Maxwell from San Antonio for an 
undisclosed sum, said Houston General Manager Steve Patterson. 
</P>
<P>
The Rockets will get the Cavaliers' 1992 or 1994 second-round draft pick, plus 
Boston's 1991 and 1993 second-round picks, which Cleveland had acquired from 
New Jersey for Dudley. 
</P>
<P>
Chievous was the Rockets' 1988 first-round draft pick. He averaged 5.9 points 
and 1.8 rebounds in 41 games for Houston this season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TRADES (SPORTS); BASKETBALL PLAYERS; NATIONAL BASKETBALL ASSOCIATION 
</P>
