<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLEWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Barr Sings the King: Two of the tabloids' favorite subjects -- Roseanne Barr 
and Elvis -- will be on display for a three-night stand in San Carlos, Calif., 
starting today. 
</P>
<P>
It will be Barr's first stand-up show in three years and she plans to sing an 
Elvis tribute as part of her act, which also will include new husband Tom 
Arnold as an Elvis impersonator. "I'm singing," Barr said. "I know my fans have 
waited a long time to hear that." BETH KLEID 
</P>
