<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: AZTECS SCORE FIVE IN 7TH, SHUT OUT CAL LUTHERAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Diego State baseball team scored five runs in the seventh inning and 
shut out Cal Lutheran, 7-0, at Smith Field Wednesday. Jeff Barry was two for 
four with an RBI in the first innning and a run in the seventh for SDSU (8-1). 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran is 4-2. 
</P>
<P>
FOOTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Martin Moss was named football coach at San Diego City College, President 
Jeanne L. Atherton announced. Moss, formerly a part-time coach, replaces 
co-head coaches Anthony Williams and Leroy Dotson, who will continue coaching 
on Moss' staff. 
</P>
<P>
Moss, a Lincoln High and UCLA graduate, was a defensive lineman for the Detroit 
Lions from 1982-85. 
</P>
<P>
RUGBY 
</P>
<P>
Four Old Mission Beach Athletic Club rugby players were chosen for the United 
States national rugby team. Chris Lippert, Bill Leversee, Rick Crivellone and 
Kevin Higgins, who was named team captain, were among 21 players chosen out of 
40 at tryouts held last weekend in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
The team will travel to Ireland to play the Irish Students on March 2 and 
Ireland's B team on March 10. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Resuming a match that was rained out on Sunday, UC San Diego split its singles 
matches with visiting Air Force, but dropped all three doubles matches and 
lost, 6-3, at UCSD. 
</P>
<P>
Triton No. 1 player Francois Monnar defeated Tony Krawietz, 6-3, 7-6 (7-5), No. 
2 Chris Belloli defeated Ricky Koda, 3-6, 6-3, 6-4, and No. 5 Tim Ditzler 
defeated Tom Jahn, 7-6 (7-5), 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
UCSD fell to 2-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
