<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There were four winning tickets purchased in Southern California for the 
$67-million jackpot in the midweek Lotto 6/49 drawing Wednesday night, lottery 
officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
The tickets, each worth about $16.7 million, were bought in Laguna Niguel, Los 
Angeles, Long Beach and Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Lotto officials said the winning ticket purchased in Orange County was bought 
at a Circle K store on Crown Valley Parkway in Laguna Niguel. 
</P>
<P>
The winning numbers picked in the twice-weekly game were 44, 27, 34, 12, 21, 41 
and the bonus number, 6. 
</P>
<P>
The numbers were chosen during a television broadcast originating in 
Sacramento. The numbers are listed in the order they were announced, but any 
combination would win. 
</P>
<P>
There were 39 tickets with five numbers plus the bonus number, each worth a 
$231,448 share of a $9.02-million prize pool. 
