<P>
BIRTH OF 2-HEADED GIRL REPORTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SOFIA, Bulgaria 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A southeast Bulgarian woman has given birth to a girl with two heads, the 
official news agency BTA reported today. 
</P>
<P>
The baby, delivered by Cesarean section, is well and feeding normally, said the 
news agency, quoting doctors at the Chirpan hospital where she was born. 
</P>
<P>
The news agency reported that the surgeon who delivered the baby said a second, 
partially formed head was growing from the head of the otherwise normal infant 
in what the doctor described as a "well-known malformation in the medical 
practice." 
</P>
<P>
"The second head has no ears, eyes or nose but has its own brain," Dr. Peter 
Vulkanov was quoted as saying. 
</P>
<P>
The report did not say when the infant was born or whether surgery was planned 
to remove the second head. 
</P>
</TEXT>
