</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Talk show host Regis Philbin, who has ribbed pregnant co-host Kathie Lee 
Gifford about her burgeoning belly over the past few months, will get the 
tables turned on him. 
</P>
<P>
In what's being billed as a Day-In-The-Life of a Pregnant Man, Philbin on 
Monday will strap on a 35-pound "Empathy Belly," a device designed specifically 
for men to experience the severe discomforts of pregnancy -- including fetal 
kicks and pressure on the kidneys. 
</P>
<P>
According to a spokesman for the "Live With Regis and Kathie Lee," Philbin will 
wear his belly all day, not just during the taping. A camera crew will follow 
Philbin around New York as he attends business meetings, a power lunch with his 
agent at a prominent Manhattan restaurant and an afternoon piano lesson before 
going home. The footage will air Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
It will be the first child for Kathie Lee, wife of ABC sportscaster Frank 
Gifford. 
</P>
